strong>$1,999/£1,899</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Apple Studio Display</td><td><strong>nano-texture</strong></td><td><strong>tilt-only adjustable</strong></td><td><strong>$1,899/£1,749</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Apple Studio Display</td><td><strong>nano-texture</strong></td><td><strong>VESA wall mount adapter</strong></td><td><strong>$1,899/£1,749</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Apple Studio Display</td><td><strong>nano-texture</strong></td><td><strong>tilt and height-adjustable</strong></td><td><strong>$2,299/£2,149</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the box, you’ll get a 1-meter Thunderbolt cable, and the nano-texture displays include Apple’s <a href=\"https://smile.amazon.com/Apple-MM6F3AM-A-Polishing-Cloth/dp/B09JQRJ15H?tag=macworld05-20&amp;asc_refurl=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">Polishing Cloth</a>. The power cable is attached to the monitor.</p>\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://images.macworld.co.uk/cmsdata/features/3814136/where_to_buy_apple_studio_display_thumb.jpg\" alt=\"Apple Studio Display and Mac Studio\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption>The Studio Display is designed to work with the new Mac Studio, but it can work with other Macs.</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Best deals on the Apple Studio Display</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s rare to find deals on Apple displays, so if you’re shopping specifically for an Apple display and a deal pops up, it’s time to take advantage.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Amazon U.S. is currently offering a few deals on the Apple Studio Display. You can save $150 or $300 dollars, which is significant when you consider that these displays almost never go on sale. Here are links to the deals:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>U.S.:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Amazon, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Apple-Studio-Display-Standard-Height-Adjustable/dp/B09V3GZD32?tag=macworld05-20&amp;asc_refurl=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Apple Studio Display (Standard Glass, Tilt-Adjustable Stand​)</a>: $1,499 ($100 off, MSRP $1,599)</li></ul>\n\n\n\n